    "Battery positive connects to B+ pad on back, ground to B- (GND)",
    "ZMK is the recommended firmware -- full wireless support including BLE profiles"
  ],
  "features": [
    "Drop-in Pro Micro replacement",
    "Built-in LiPo charging (100mA)",
    "Native USB-C + BLE 5.0 on single chip",
    "256KB RAM, 1MB flash",
    "21 usable GPIO pins",
    "First-class ZMK firmware support",
    "UF2 bootloader — drag-and-drop firmware flashing"
  ],
  "concerns": [
    "Charging limited to 100mA — slow for batteries >500mAh",
    "No onboard antenna — uses PCB trace antenna",
    "Premium price ($25) compared to clones",
    "21 GPIOs limits matrix size for larger keyboards",
    "Occasionally out of stock"
  ],
